<node CREATED="1728658275660" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1903934470" MODIFIED="1728752737203" TEXT="**GENERIC SOFTWARE CREATION PHASES**">
<font BOLD="true" NAME="IBM Plex Sans Cond" SIZE="14"/>
<attribute NAME="type" VALUE="expander"/>
<node CREATED="1728658310113" ID="ID_1149063529" MODIFIED="1728744789944" TEXT="#### Generic S/W Creation Workflow Phases&#xa;&#xa;##### Phase 1:** Evaluate Problem Drivers&#xa;  * **Identify the problem:**&#xa;Assemble a team to &#xa;    * define the problem statement, &#xa;    * identify key stakeholders, and &#xa;    * contextualize the solution.&#xa;  * **Gain input and opinions:** Engage stakeholders and experts to understand &#xa;    * the problem drivers, &#xa;    * required features, and &#xa;    * desired outcomes.&#xa;  * **Define the problem scope:** Establish the &#xa;    * problem scope, &#xa;    * boundaries, and &#xa;    * constraints.&#xa;  * **Outline the technical requirements:** Define the technical requirements, including &#xa;    * data structures, &#xa;    * algorithms, and &#xa;    ** software architecture.&#xa;  * **Identify potential risks and challenges:** Assess &#xa;    * potential risks and &#xa;    * challenges associated with the solution.&#xa;&#xa;##### Phase 2:** Develop the Software Creation Workflows&#xa;  * **Establish a workflow template:** Refine a generic workflow template to accommodate different &#xa;    * project sizes, &#xa;    * complexity, and &#xa;    * requirements.&#xa;  * **Define the software creation process:** Establish a step-by-step process for creating software, including &#xa;    * planning, &#xa;    * design, &#xa;    * development, &#xa;    * testing, and &#xa;    * deployment.&#xa;  * **Create a decision-making framework:** Develop a __framework for making decisions during the software creation workflow.__&#xa;  * **Develop a content management system:** Create a __system for documenting and managing software development knowledge__, including &#xa;    * code documentation, &#xa;    * technical specifications, and &#xa;    * project management notes.&#xa;&#xa;##### Phase 3:** Iterate and Refine the Workflow&#xa;  * **Integrate and test the workflow:** Integrate the workflow template and implement the decision-making framework throughout the workflow.&#xa;  * **Test and validate the workflow:** Conduct regular testing and validation to ensure the workflow meets the problem drivers and stakeholders&apos; expectations.&#xa;  * **Refine and iterate the workflow:** Iterate and refine the workflow to address any issues or challenges that arise during the development process.&#xa;  * **Develop a training and documentation model:** Create a training plan and documentation framework to facilitate the adoption and maintenance of the workflow.&#xa;&#xa;##### Phase 4:** Implement and Deploy the Software&#xa;  * **Develop a deployment plan:** Establish a plan for deploying the software, including infrastructure provisioning, service management, and data migration.&#xa;  * **Implement the software creation workflow:** Integrate the defined workflow into the existing software development lifecycle, ensuring seamless handoffs between the planning, design, development, testing, and deployment stages.&#xa;  * **Manage the software creation workflow&apos;s governance:** Establish a governance model for managing the workflow&apos;s activities, including monitoring performance, tracking progress, and enforcing architectural constraints.&#xa;&#xa;##### Phase 5:** Monitor and Evaluate the Software Creation Workflow&#xa;  * **Implement metrics and analytics:** Track key metrics and analytics to evaluate the effectiveness of the workflow, identifying areas for improvement.&#xa;  * **Host regular monitoring sessions:** Conduct regular monitoring sessions to discuss the workflow&apos;s progress, resolve issues, and refine the process.&#xa;  * **Create a best practices repository:** Document the workflow&apos;s best practices, lessons learned, and case studies for the Software Creation Process.">
<attribute NAME="type" VALUE="explanation"/>
</node>
</node>
